  "texts": [
    "Liquid chromatographic separation of samples was performed on ACQUITY UPLC Protein BEH C4 column (300 Å pore diameter, 1.7 µm, 2.1 × 50 mm, Waters) using gradient elution.",
    "Then 1 µl of sample was injected with a flow rate of 0.3 ml min -1 and the analysis was carried out at default parameters.",
    "The acquired data was processed using UNIFI software.",
    "Disulfide bonds (-2 Da per bond) were detected in all variants (Extended Data Table 5).",
    "To enable BLI binding assays with streptavidin sensors, β 2 -microglobulin was biotinylated."
  ],
